S wind 1-5 mph- sunny w/ cumulus clouds- hot- humid
Partly cloudy- hazy- S wind 5 mph- 3 in. waves
Calm- no waves- cloudy- hazy but bright
Light S wind- 1-2" waves- partly cloudy- hazy- bright.
Partly cloudy- bright- W wind 10 mph- 6 in. waves- depth 29.9 ft.
Light E wind- mostly sunny- 1-3 in. waves.
Cloudy- S wind 10 mph- 3-6 in. waves
Sunny- cumulus clouds- no wind- algae conc. in top 3-6 in. of water- no mixing
Northwest wind 5-10 mph- 3-6 in. waves- windrows- partly cloudy- sun behind cloud during reading
Wind calm- partly cloudy- no waves- air 70 F
S wind 10-12 mph- 3-6 in. waves- mostly sunny
Southwest wind 10-15 mph- windrows- whitecaps- 6-12 in. waves- partly cloudy- algae blown downwind
Mostly sunny- E wind 5 mph- 1-3 in. waves- air 35 F
Southwest wind 5 mph- windrows developing- thin clouds- 200' of shore ice in N end barber's bay
Muddy from previous rains- W wind 5 mph- 1 in. waves- sampled off Colladay point
Sunny- warm- S wind 5 mph- sampled W of deep hole
Clear sky- W wind 10 mph- p.m. sample
Northeast wind 5 mph- mostly sunny- chop from holiday boats- algae on S shore
Northeast wind 5 mph- mostly sunny- green algae bloom
Partly sunny- sky 60-70% cumulus- NW wind 3 mph
Cloud cover 90%- NE wind 5 mph- hazy but bright
Southwest wind 5 mph- 90% sun- 3" waves- air 80 F
Mostly sunny- wind  less than  5 mph
E wind at 5-10mph- .5' waves- sunny- 75 F- 10% cloud cover- depth: 30.5'
S wind at 5 mph- clear- warm- humid
Sunny- S wind at 5 mph- water clearer at S side Collsday point
100% sunshine- no wind- cold the last few days.
Light wind north-northwest.  Cloudy- but hazy bright.
South-southeast wind about 10 mph- hazy and bright.
SE wind @ 5 mph- cloudy and bright.
S wind @ 5 mph- 95% sunshine- 4" of rain in the last 2 weeks- the lake is not muddy.
Very light SW wind- flat water at the site- water is muddy from recent rains.  Ice off 4-9-93.
North-northeast wind is 3-5 mph.  1" waves at site.  90% sunshine.
SE wind about 3-5 mph.  80 degrees- humid- 100% sunshine.  Brown particles in water- clumpy (algae )
Northeast wind- 1-2 mph- 100% sunshine.  Algae near the surface.
Northwest. wind is 5-10 mph- wave height is 0.5'.  95% sunshine- air temp is 64 degrees.  Major algae bloom underway.  Thick clusters near surface.  Light green.
South wind @ 5 mph- 100% cloud cover- not quite "hazy bright".  Green algae spread evenly over top few inches.
Air temp is 75 degrees- 100% sunshine- SW wind @ 2 mph.
Southwest wind - 8 mph.  Air temp is 60 degrees- 100% sunshine- waves are not a problem with the reading.
West wind- 5 mph.  100% sunshine.  Algae- thick near the surface.
Southwest wind 10-15 mph.  A few whitecaps.  Water muddy- 100% sunshine- air temp. 55 degrees.
Lake rough-secchi depth  greater than 8 +  less than 9.  SW wind ~15 mph- 100% sunshine- waves 1'- windrows.  Air temp. 60 degrees F.
100% sunshine- no wind (flat water)- ~60 degrees F- /wtcalgae "flowing" past boat in top foot of water or so.  Brown algae.
100% sunshine- very light breeze (flat water).  "long" algae in top foot or so- a little on surface- algae clumping.
Southwest wind ~10 mph.  Waves too big @ deep hole - moved to barber's bay - 80% sunshine.
Water depth=29.2'.  90% sunshine.  No wind- flat water.  See algae in top foot or so.  Not "thick" yet.
No wind- partly cloudy- hazy- bright- algae clumps near shore.
50 % sunshine.  North wind ~5 mph.  Algae bloom.  3.3" rain this week.
100% sunshine- calm.  Major algal bloom in progress.  Algae in thick strands at surface with some clumping.  Awful at west shore.  At shore thick accumulations including blue greens
North-northeast wind about 5-10 mph.  Waves less than 0.5'.  Mostly sunny- no clouds shading lake.  Some algae top foot or so.
Sunny- hot (85 degrees f).  No rain 2-3 weeks.  Light breeze from east about 1-2 mph.  Algae top foot or so.  Not thick.
SE wind ~ 5 mph- 100% sunshine @ 6: 35pm.  Rain earlier today.  Cleared about 6 pm.
Northeast wind 5-10 mph- mostly sunny 0.5' waves- air temp. low 80's.
WSW wind 5-10 mph- 100% sunshine- waves 0.5'.  Water nice cause wind mixing algae in vertical.
Southwest wind ~ 10 mph.  Waves 0.5 to 1'- sunny- warm.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Northwest wind 5-10 mph.  0.5' waves- 100% sunshine.  Depth=29'- ts 80 degrees F.
Southwest wind ~ 5 mph- mostly cloudy.  Only see 1 other boat on lake.  Temp ~= 55 degrees-60 degrees
South wind ~8 mph. 3"-6" waves. could see deeper w/o waves. 100% sunshine. air temp. =~ 60 degrees F.
South wind ~3 mph. 50% sunshine. algae "clumping". water clear between clumps.
100% sunshine. No wind. Very heavy algae. Most ever remember. Been like this for weeks. No blue greens
60 degrees- wind at less than 5 mph.  100% sunshine.
East wind 12-15 mph- 1 foot waves.  95% sunshine.  70 degrees for air temperature.
Southwest wind at 5-8 mph- 50% sunshine.  Waves 1/2 foot.  Air temperature 85 degrees.
Heavy algae on shore - no wind for 3 to 4 days
Clear- few scattered clouds. Very light wind. Suspended small clumps (1/8-1/4 inch dia) of green alage. On surface alage have approximately 15-20% coverage.
Broken clouds- wind 6.7 kts from the south- light chop. Suspended small clumps of green algae (1/8-1/4 inch dia)- about 25% by volume

Clear- wind 8.0 kts from the NNW- light chop. Suspended small clumps (1/8-3/4 inch dia) of green alage. Air temperature: 69.9 F. On June 15th observed large muddy brown plume moving ENE out of Barber Bay. By evening on June 16th it covered the norhern half of the lake. By morning of June 18th it seemed to have dissipated.
Partly cloudy- wind 6.5 kts from the southwest- very light chop. Suspended short filaments of green algae-
Partly cloudy- 68F- light chop. Suspended clump and filaments of green algae. Scattered clumps (less than 1 inch dia) blue-green algae on surface.
Clear- 73F- wind 4.6 kts from the northwest- light chop. Green alage on surface- suspended short (1/2 inch) filaments with clumps up to 1 inch.
Broken clouds- 85F- wind 5.3 kts from the westsouthwest- light chop. Suspended filaments of green algae (1/2-3/4 inch long)
Partly cloudy- 80F- wind 7.3 kts from the southwest- light chop. Scattered blue-green algae up to 1 inch dia- suspended clumps and filaments of green algae (3/4 inch dia)
Partly cloudy; 76F; wind ssw- 7.7 kts; moderate chop. Suspended short filaments of green algae
Broken clouds; 77.9 F; wind 4.2 kt- SE- light chop; suspended short filaments of green alage
78F- Partly cloudy- wind 6.0 kts from the southeast- light chop; suspended short filiments and small clumps of green algae.
78F- Mostly cloudy- wind 3.8 kts from the southwest- light chop; suspended short filiments green algae- some blue-green algae near shore.
66 F; Partly cloudy- wind 3.3 kts from the northnorthwest- very light chop; Suspended small particles of green algae.
65 F; clear- wind 9.4 kts from the southwest- moderate to heavy chop; Suspended small particles of green algae.
67 F; Partly cloudy- hazy- wind 6.7 kts from the southeast- light chop; Suspended small particles of green algae.
60.8F; partly cloudy- wind 3 kts from southwest- very light chop;  water clear.

Scattered clouds; 66F; wind light and variable; water smooth. Small (less than 1/8 inches) particles of green algae both suspended and on the surface over much of the lake.  Larger clumps of green algae along the South shore.
Air temperature 75F; clear- few scattered clouds; wind NNW at 5.4 kts; moderate chop. small (up to 1/2 inches) particles of green algae suspended in the water column.

Air temperature 76F; partly cloudy; wind light and variable-. 1/2 inch to 1 inch clumps of green algae on the surface- small particles suspended in the water column- with some larger clumps- small to large patches of blue-green algae; weed cutters in operation.

Air temperature 74F- broken clouds; wind light and variable- small (up to 1/2 inches) particles of green algae covering most of surface- large clumps suspended in the water column; some blue-green algae on the surface near the south shore
Air temperture 73F; scattered clouds; wind WNW at 7.3 kts; moderate chop. small (less than 1/8 inches) particles of green algae suspended in the water column.
Air temperture 78F; high scattered clouds; wind SSE at 7.5 kts; moderate chop. small (less than 1/8 inches) particles of green algae suspended in the water column.
Air temperature 75F clear- few scattered clouds; wind SSE at 4.47 Kts; light chop. fine particles of green algae suspended in the water column.
Air temperature 65F- clear- scattered clouds; wind light and variable. fine particles of green algae floating on the surface suspended in the water column.
Fine particles of algae on the surface and suspended in the water column- partly cloudy- light chop- winds from ESE at 5.7 knots- 69F
Air temperature 59F; scattered clouds; wind light and variable-. small particles (less than 1/4 inches) of green algae  suspended in the water column. Sighting of sand hill cranes.
Air temperature 59F; broken clouds; wind WSW at 5.4 kts; light chop.  Small particles (1/4? to 1/2?) of green algae suspended in water column.
Air temperature819F;sky clear; wind SSW at 5.8 kts; moderate chop. Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae suspended in water column.
Air temperature 67.1F;broken clouds; wind SE at 1.4 kts; very light chop. Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae suspended in water column.

Air temperature 80 degrees F;clear sky; wind SSW at  5.3 kts; light chop. Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/4") of green algae suspended in water column. Mats of floating algae along Lund's Point. Floating green and blue/green algae along the south shore
Air temperature 80.9 F; scattered clouds; wind NW at 8.6 kts;  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae on surface and suspended in water column.
Air temperature 80.2 F; scattered clouds; wind NW at 3.0  kts; light chop.  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae on surface and suspended in water column.
Air temperature 77 F; scattered clouds; wind ENE at 4.1K. light chop.;  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae on surface and suspended in water column.
Air temperature 79 F; scattered clouds;haze  wind SW at 1.3  kts; Slight chop;  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae on surface and suspended in water column.
Air temperature 78 F; scattered clouds; wind WSW at 6.8 kts; Moderate chop;  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae suspended in water column.
Air temperature 72 F; scattered clouds; wind W at 2.1 kts; Light chop;  Scattered small particles ( greater than 1/8') of green algae suspended in water column. Areas of loose floating weeds.
Clouds: Scattered high cirrus- Wind: ESE- 6.2Kt- Air temperature: 72.6F; Moderate chop- Some particles of green algae (up to 1/8") suspended in water column
Clouds: Scattered high cirrus- Wind: ENE- 4.4Kt- Air temperature: 79.7F; Light to moderate chop- Small particles of green algae ( less than  1/8") suspended in water column
Clouds: Scattered high cirrus- Wind: SE @ 9.3Kt- Air temperature: 78.0F; Moderate broken chop- Small particles of green algae (less than 1/16") suspended in water column
Clouds: Scattered cumulus- Wind: W- 4.6Kt- Air temperature: 84.1F; Moderate chop- Very small particles of green algae (less than 1/16") suspended in water column
Clear- Wind: NNW- 5.0Kt- Air temperature: Ukn; Light chop- Some particles of green algae (up to 1/8") suspended in water column

Clear- Wind: SW- 6.9Kt- Air temperature: 81.4F; Light chop- Small particles of green algae (up to 1/16") suspended in water column.  Many white bass floating on surface and associated with patches of algae bloom.
Clouds: Scattered cumulus- Wind: E- 1.1Kt- Air temperature: 72.6F; Surface smooth- Small particles of green algae (up to 1/16") suspended in water column.  Few white bass floating on surface
Clouds: Scattered cumulus- Wind: S- 3.0Kt- Air temperature: 82.6F; Surface glassy- Some small particles of green algae (up to 1/16") suspended in water column
